Plum Cooking TemperaturePublished on September 2, 2023 1:30 AM GMT<br/><br/><p>在<a href="https://www.jefftk.com/p/making-prunes">去年</a><span>享受了烹饪/烘干李子的乐趣后</span>，我决定今年再尝试一次。这次我比较了两种不同的烹饪整个李子的方法：140华氏度约1.5天，350华氏度约1.5小时。</p><p>我很好奇温度越高是好还是坏。也许有趣的味道会随着温度的升高而消失，或者可能会随着时间的延长而消失？也许这些方法的不同之处在于它们如何将淀粉转化为糖？</p><p>这是我将 350F 李子从托盘中取出时的照片：</p><p> <a href="https://www.jefftk.com/roasted-plums-tray-350f-big.jpg"><img src="https://res.cloudinary.com/lesswrong-2-0/image/upload/f_auto,q_auto/v1/mirroredImages/3etri4vCgaPcr84uE/z9u0fprjdlrcf73weygz" srcset="https://res.cloudinary.com/lesswrong-2-0/image/upload/f_auto,q_auto/v1/mirroredImages/3etri4vCgaPcr84uE/z9u0fprjdlrcf73weygz 550w, https://res.cloudinary.com/lesswrong-2-0/image/upload/f_auto,q_auto/v1/mirroredImages/3etri4vCgaPcr84uE/e92sqfj9tndeqh6ayzkt 1100w"></a></p><div></div><p></p><p>将它们取出后，我手动去除果核，并确保用抹刀刮平锅以获得美味的果汁。</p><p>以下是<a href="https://www.jefftk.com/p/no-more-freezer-pucks">准备重新装袋的</a>图片，左侧为 350F，右侧为 140F：</p><p> <a href="https://www.jefftk.com/roasted-plums-350f-vs-140f-big.jpg"><img src="https://res.cloudinary.com/lesswrong-2-0/image/upload/f_auto,q_auto/v1/mirroredImages/3etri4vCgaPcr84uE/hgjiyr05dlfh8zeorhiv" srcset="https://res.cloudinary.com/lesswrong-2-0/image/upload/f_auto,q_auto/v1/mirroredImages/3etri4vCgaPcr84uE/hgjiyr05dlfh8zeorhiv 550w, https://res.cloudinary.com/lesswrong-2-0/image/upload/f_auto,q_auto/v1/mirroredImages/3etri4vCgaPcr84uE/dcof4wpgqxym3lievmun 1100w"></a></p><div></div><p></p><p>我做了一些测试，人们不知道哪个是哪个：</p><p> <a href="https://www.jefftk.com/plum-sauce-comparison-big.jpg"><img src="https://res.cloudinary.com/lesswrong-2-0/image/upload/f_auto,q_auto/v1/mirroredImages/3etri4vCgaPcr84uE/o4q7meeziyuodag22obr" srcset="https://res.cloudinary.com/lesswrong-2-0/image/upload/f_auto,q_auto/v1/mirroredImages/3etri4vCgaPcr84uE/o4q7meeziyuodag22obr 550w, https://res.cloudinary.com/lesswrong-2-0/image/upload/f_auto,q_auto/v1/mirroredImages/3etri4vCgaPcr84uE/gh8c1970vrvum5ww75pl 1100w"></a></p><div></div><p></p><p>总的来说，每个人都更喜欢 350F：更浓郁的李子味。一位品尝者认为 140F 有点“怪异”的味道。 350F 的甜度较低，足以让您不想直接使用许多菜肴，但稍后加糖调味并不难。</p><p> （350F 在后勤方面也更容易——把烤箱绑起来一天以上并不是很好的室友行为。）</p><br/><br/><a href="https://www.lesswrong.com/posts/3etri4vCgaPcr84uE/plum-cooking-temperature#comments">讨论</a>; https://www.lesswrong.com/posts/3etri4vCgaPcr84uE/plum-cooking-Temperature 3etri4vCgaPcr84uEjefftk Sat, 02 Sep 2023 01:30:05 GMT 
What did you learn from leaked documents?Published on September 2, 2023 1:28 AM GMT<br/><br/><p>作为理性主义者，我们寻求理解世界，但政治偏见和不同的议程使理解世界变得更加困难。</p><p>泄露的文件代表了一种基本事实，展示了世界的真实运作方式。告诉我们什么在出售，真正的议程是什么，间谍有多强大，以及政府的协调程度如何。它们几乎与阴谋论相反，因为它们提出的观察结果可以消除阴谋论。</p><p>不过文档太多看不下去了，大家互相切磋吧。是什么让你感到惊讶并促使你更新你的世界观？</p><br/><br/> <a href="https://www.lesswrong.com/posts/NgDdyy3NxykbntQyJ/what-did-you-learn-from-leaked-documents#comments">讨论</a>; https://www.lesswrong.com/posts/NgDdyy3NxykbntQyJ/what-did-you-learn-from-leaked-documents NgDdyy3NxykbntQyJwassname Sat, 02 Sep 2023 01:28:48 GMT 
